                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.113/1307: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-18T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 18, 1931—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>237. Legation’s 417, July 11, 4 p.m. Will you instruct the Consulates General at
                    Canton and Hong Kong to report through the Legation by mail or by telegraph
                    important instances of arms, munitions, and airplanes, whether military or
                    commercial, being shipped from the United States or from other foreign countries
                    to the Cantonese authorities; and likewise to report cases of commercial
                    airplanes which have been found in use for military purposes.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
